<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<worksheet xml:id="app4-reading" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>APP-4 Reading</title>
    <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Things you should understand and know:
        <ul>
            <li>Explain the meaning of Stokes' Theorem</li>
            <li>Explain the meaning of the Divergence Theorem</li>
        </ul></p>
        <p>Things you should be able to do:
        <ul>
            <li>Use Stokes' Theorem to evaluate a line integral</li>
            <li>Use Stokes' Theorem to calculate a surface integral</li>
            <li>Use Stokes' Theorem to calculate a curl</li>
            <li>Use the Divergence Theorem to calculate the flux of a vector field</li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
      <li><p>You will be assessed on the following criteria:
        <ul>
          <li><p>Problem structure: Solution should be organized and easy to follow, with clear, complete steps 
              that follow progressively from one to the next.</p></li>
          <li><p>Stokes' Theorem: Be able to apply Stokes' Theorem to evaluate line integrals, surface integrals, and curls.</p></li>
          <li><p>Apply Stokes' Theorem to find a given surface integral.</p></li>
            <li><p>The Divergence Theorem: Understand the Divergence Theorem and apply it to find the flux of a vector field.</p></li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </objectives>
        <p>All of the readings for this course come from the OpenStax Calculus 
            Volume 3 textbook, which is available for free online at 
            <url href="https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3">
                https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3</url>. You 
                can read the textbook online or download a PDF version. 
                The textbook is also available in print from various retailers 
                if you prefer a physical copy.</p> 
        <p>For this lesson, you should read sections <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/6-7-stokes-theorem">
            6.7 Stokes' Theorem</url> and <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/6-8-divergence-theorem">
            6.8 The Divergence Theorem</url>. You should read through the sections carefully, 
            making sure to understand the definitions, examples, and key ideas. 
            You should also work through the exercises at the end of each section 
            to test your understanding and practice applying the concepts. Some of the 
            exercises at the end of the section are assigned in the WP assignments.</p>      
</worksheet>
